text: <@U02618EV1>: assets will be added as smart objects to PSD files, is this okay?
Let me know if this creates more work for you.

No problem. They don't have to include the assets inside the PSDs. You may want to let them know that they can just send us the files in a folder. I image that may be easier for them and us. Either way is fine with me.
<@U026AP8CM> also please remind them that we can't use blendmodes on the web. I mention that b/c some of the UI items in the PSDs use blenmodes. The designer will know what I mean :wink:

<@U026AP8CM>: I don't want to speak for Gaston, but will try. :wink:
Blend modes are photoshop blends such as multiply, overlay, etc. They are often used to make something look good but don't necessarily translate into usable web material
